            <h4>📚 About This Encyclopedia</h4>
            <p>A comprehensive, merged collection of Information Systems theories essential for PhD comprehensive exams.
                Each theory includes: <strong>foundational origins</strong>, <strong>theoretical core</strong>,
                <strong>evolution in IS research</strong>, <strong>critical analysis</strong>,
                and <strong>practical exam applications</strong>. This encyclopedia merges insights from multiple
                courses including BCIS 6670, 6680, and 6360.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>🎯 How to use:</strong> Browse by category below, use search (Ctrl+K),
                or jump to specific theories. Each entry includes exam-ready examples and measurement strategies.</p>
